                <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115(39)/128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 14, 1939—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>880. Your Nos. 2020 and 2030, November 10 and November 11. Department has
                    hesitated to suggest to large number of importers a procedure involving expense
                    on their part and large amount of work for Department without some indication
                    such efforts will be advantageous. However, because of your urgings they are now
                    being requested to file such affidavits and supporting evidence in duplicate,
                    one copy to go to Consul General at Hamburg by mail, the substance to be
                    telegraphed to him as soon as there is any definite indication such telegraphic
                    communications will serve any purpose. See, in this connection, Department’s
                    cables of November 10th to Consul General reply to which is being awaited with
                    interest.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
